25|$|Instant-runoff voting was devised in 1871 by American {{architect}} William Robert Ware, {{although it}} is, in effect, {{a special case}} of the <b>single</b> <b>transferable</b> <b>vote</b> method, which emerged independently in the 1850s. Unlike the <b>single</b> <b>transferable</b> <b>vote</b> in multi-seat elections, however, the only ballot transfers are from backers of candidates who have been eliminated.|$|E
